One thing I took from this strong, invigorating Vinyasa practice is an awareness of how challenging other, slower practices really are! I think some people assume softer, slower practices are easier or less challenging, but what I've come to realize is that constant movement like this absolutely flies by for me, no matter how hard it is, whereas slow moving practices force me to quiet, pay attention, and build endurance in a way that is incredibly counter to how many of us live our daily lives. I think my concepts of "easy" and "hard" fitness have not only become more flexible, but have almost reversed over the five months(!) that I've been doing daily yoga with Adriene. Just a little thought that came to me as I was moving through this wonderful flow.
